The gloves are covered with small copper rivets.  The wearer may use the gloves to throw a sharp electric jolt at a nearby target.

The Tumblers were a group of assassins who worked together to topple rich, powerful nobles and merchants. Emperor Fenias IV used them to regain control over the various provinces of Valratha, whose nobles had become almost entirely independent of the crown.

Samile the Nervous was a golddigger known for surviving the betrayal of at least five partners. He always seemed to be aware of what was going on, seconds before anyone else did. Being successful at finding gold made him wealthy, but he was never happy. Always disgusted with humanity, Samile would complain bitterly to anyone who would listen. Some would comment that it was more likely this barrage of complaints that drove his partners to try to kill him, more than greed.
